---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-agra.html" headerVariant="guide">

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">Local Solar Guide · Agra, Uttar Pradesh</div>
<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">Rooftop Solar in Agra</h1>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Agra homeowners are cutting DVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies. This guide covers costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Check My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</section>

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">DVVNL</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Dakshinanchal / UPPCL</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Agra</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Strong Solar Irradiance</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Agra receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day — one of the higher figures in India. The dry, sunny climate of the Yamuna basin provides consistent solar generation across most months of the year, with peak output in April–September.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">High Summer Electricity Bills</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Agra's extreme summer heat drives intensive air conditioning use, making DVVNL bills among the highest of the year from April to June. Solar generation peaks through precisely these months, making the financial alignment particularly strong for Agra households.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Rising DVVNL Tariffs</h3><p class="text-slate-600">DVVNL domestic electricity tariffs have risen with successive UP SERC revisions. Installing rooftop solar now protects your household from future tariff increases by generating a portion of your electricity at near-zero cost for 25 years.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Eligibility</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Agra homeowners with a DVVNL residential connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy. DVVNL maintains an empanelled installer list for Agra on pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">DVVNL Net Metering in Agra</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Agra homeowners under DVVNL.</p>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via DVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your installer must be empanelled with DVVNL under the PM Surya Ghar scheme. Verify on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to DVVNL</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to DVVNL with system technical details. Most empanelled installers handle this on your behalf.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">DVVNL Technical Inspection</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A DVVNL engineer inspects the installation to verify grid safety compliance. Timelines in Agra typically run two to four weeks depending on DISCOM workload.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your existing DVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter measuring both import and export. A one-time meter replacement fee may apply.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once commissioned by DVVNL, surplus solar exported to the grid earns credits on your monthly DVVNL electricity bill.</p></div></div>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">See our <a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a> for a full explanation of how credits work on your bill.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Choosing the Right System Size in Agra</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly DVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly DVVNL Bill</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area Needed</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th></tr></thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr><td class="p-4">₹800 – ₹2,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="1kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">1kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">80–120 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small homes, limited roof</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹1,500 – ₹3,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small families, 2BHK</td></tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50"><td class="p-4">₹2,500 – ₹5,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td><td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Medium families, 3BHK</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹4,000 – ₹7,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Larger homes, heavy AC use</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a> for the full methodology.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Agra</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Agra homeowners with a DVVNL connection can apply for the central subsidy through pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW at lower per-kW rate</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div></div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as an Agra Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your DVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select a DVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal's list</li>
<li>3. Get system installed, net metering connected, DVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited to your bank account — typically weeks to months</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">Subsidy amounts are subject to government policy. Verify current rates at pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
</div>
<div class="mt-4"><a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →</a></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Agra Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">We help homeowners across Agra understand solar options and connect with DVVNL-empanelled installers.</p>
<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{["Civil Lines", "Kamla Nagar", "Shahganj", "Bodla", "Sikandra", "Dayalbagh", "Trans Yamuna Colony", "Kalindi Vihar", "Tajnagari", "Shastripuram", "Sanjay Place", "Sultanpura", "Lohamandi"].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Agra Solar</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Agra?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Agra falls under <strong>DVVNL (Dakshinanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a UPPCL subsidiary covering southern Uttar Pradesh. All net metering applications and PM Surya Ghar empanelment for Agra homeowners are processed through DVVNL. This is the same DISCOM as Kanpur.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering with DVVNL in Agra?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation by a DVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering application to DVVNL. DVVNL inspects the system and installs a bi-directional meter. The process typically takes two to four weeks in Agra.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Agra?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Agra homeowners with a DVVNL connection are eligible. Use a DVVNL-empanelled installer and apply at pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current subsidy amounts before applying.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Agra homes?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">For typical Agra homes with monthly DVVNL bills of ₹1,500–₹4,000, a 2kW to 3kW system is most appropriate. The city's hot summers mean homes with significant AC use often benefit from 3kW systems.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Agra?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pre-subsidy cost for a quality on-grid system in Agra typically ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW. After PM Surya Ghar central subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Compare quotes from at least two DVVNL-empanelled installers.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is Agra a good location for solar?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Agra receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day and has one of the sunniest climates in UP. Extreme summers — when DVVNL bills are highest — align perfectly with peak solar output, making rooftop solar financially very effective for Agra homeowners.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-10">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
<p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Also serving homeowners in <a href="rooftop-solar-kanpur.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Kanpur</a> — also under DVVNL with the same net metering process. <a href="cities.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">View all city guides →</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Helpful Guides for Agra Homeowners</h2>
<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Subsidies</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">PM Surya Ghar Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Billing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Net Metering Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/solar-inverter-types-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Equipment</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Solar Inverter Types</div></a>
<a href="learn/how-to-choose-solar-installer.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Installers</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">How to Choose an Installer</div></a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-[2rem] p-10">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">See How Much You Can Save in Agra</h2>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-8">Get a personalised solar savings estimate based on your DVVNL bill — in under 60 seconds.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Calculate My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
